  "bodyHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">We&#39;ve updated our Trade-in grading guidelines to improve clarity between customer declarations and refurbisher expectations, and to better standardize counteroffer practices.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">The complete guidelines are attached to this article. They include:<b></b></span></h2>\n<p> </p>\n<ul><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Clear grading definitions and rules</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Visual examples</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Tips to decrease the Counteroffer Rate and increase the Counteroffer Acceptance Rate</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Definition of non-spottable issues</span></li></ul>\n<h2><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Grade definitions for refurbishers</span></h2>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"border-color: #000000;border-style: solid;width: 100.059%;\" border=\"1\"><thead><tr><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Grade number</span></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Grade name</span></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 46.511%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Cosmetic condition for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">refurbishers</span></span></th><th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 24.9299%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Functional condition for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">refurbishers</span></span></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">0</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Functional - Flawless</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 46.511%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">A few faint signs of wear, not noticeable from 8 inches away</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"4\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 24.9299%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">All features are functional with non-spottable issues</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">1</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Functional - Very good</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 46.511%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Signs of wear, including deep scratches and/or dents</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">2</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Functional - Used</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">3</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Functional - Cracked</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 46.511%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">One or more cracks and the screen can have defective pixels, ghost touch, screen burn-in, dead pixels, touch issues</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">4</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Not functional - Broken parts with scratches</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 46.511%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Signs of wear, including deep scratches and/or dents on the outside of the device</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 24.9299%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Not 100% Functional</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;text-align: center;width: 8.80607%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">5</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 19.7206%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">Not functional - Broken parts with cracks</span></td><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"border-color: #000000;width: 46.511%;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 13px;color: #000000;\">One or more cracks and the screen can have defective pixels, ghost touch, screen burn-in, dead pixels, touch issues</span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 id=\"h_01FRNDHXFWRA8G12294RBCQE35\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><strong>Key Updates &amp; information</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Different Grade Definitions</span></h3>\n<div style=\"left: 20px;top: 123.984px;\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Important: There are now different grading definitions for customers and refurbishers.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Most customers aren&#39;t grading experts and are likely to overestimate their device&#39;s condition. We have therefore differentiated customers’ and refurbishers’ grade definitions for you to have more realistic expectations.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">This includes:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"> </span></p>\n<ul><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">When customers declare a device “Functional - Flawless”, it can have a few faint signs of wear</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">When customers declare a device “Functional - Very good”, it can have deep scratches, like a “Functional - Used” device.</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">When customers declare &quot;All features functional,&quot; refurbishers should expect &quot;All features functional with non-spottable issues&quot;</span></li></ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Note: We are keeping stricter definitions for customers to maximize the quality of the phones you will receive on each grade.</span></p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"></span></h3>\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Counteroffer Restrictions</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Important: This comes as a consequence of the updated Grade Definitions</span></p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"></span></h3>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">You <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">CANNOT</span> </strong>make a counteroffer in these situations:</span>\n<p> </p>\n<ul><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Grade 0 (Functional - Flawless): Devices received with a few faint signs of wear</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Grade 1 (Functional - Very Good): Devices with signs of wear or deep scratches</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Non-spottable issues (weak vibration, muffled audio, false contacts, etc.)</span></li><li style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;color: #000000;\">Battery condition, unofficial parts, non-EU products, or locked devices</span></li></ul>\n</div>"
}